{"lemma":"فَخْر","slug":"فَخْر","root":"ف.خ.ر","root_slug":"ف-خ-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-خ-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33194","","n33199","n33200"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%AE%D9%92%D8%B1"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to glory; to boast; to be proud"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pride, honour, glory"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"something of high renown or fame"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"passage of poetry praising a group or individual"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ف خ ر (f ḵ r). See the root for etymology."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33194","headword_ar":"فَخَرَ","root":"fxr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxorN","text_ar":"فَخْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxarN","text_ar":"فَخَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxaArN","text_ar":"فَخَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or this is a simple subst., (Msb,) or it is a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fixaArN","text_ar":"فِخَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to some, and this may be an inf. n. either of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxara","text_ar":"فَخَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for there are many instances of the same kind, or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAxara","text_ar":"فَاخَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxaArN","text_ar":"فَخَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h, is post-classical, and therefore not allowable, (Th, O,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxaArapN","text_ar":"فَخَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fix~iyraY","text_ar":"فِخِّيرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fix~iyraA='u","text_ar":"فِخِّيرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aftxr","text_ar":"افتخر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tfAxr","text_ar":"تفاخر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ftH","text_ar":"فتح"},{"kind":"text","text":";) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gloried,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boasted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he gloried in, boasted of, boasted himself in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"praised"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commended himself for, certain properties,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"particular qualities:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he enumerated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recounted, the particulars of his ancestral nobility"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eminence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his own glorious"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honourable deeds"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"qualities:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he arrogated to himself greatness and nobility:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he contended for superiority by reason of honours arising from memorable deeds"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"qualities, and from parentage"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relationship, and other things relating to himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to his ancestors:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he contended for superiority by reason of things extrinsic to himself, such as wealth, and rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxarotu bihi","text_ar":"فَخَرْتُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gloried in it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (Msb.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tfAxr","text_ar":"تفاخر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimaA Einodahu","text_ar":"بِمَا عِنْدَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gloried in, boasted of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boasted himself in, what he possessed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ftH","text_ar":"فتح"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxara baEoDuhumo EalaY baEoDK","text_ar":"فَخَرَ بَعْضُهُمْ عَلَى بَعْضٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One party of them boasted against another"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bika*aA","text_ar":"بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (K.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxara","text_ar":"فَخَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxorN","text_ar":"فَخْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He magnified himself by boasting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAxarahu fafaxarahu","text_ar":"فَاخَرَهُ فَفَخَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K, [in two copies of the S written"},{"kind":"text","text":", contrary to analogy in a verb signifying surpassing in a contest, accord. to most of the grammarians,]) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxorN","text_ar":"فَخْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) see 3. ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxara fulaAnN","text_ar":"فَخَرَ فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyawoma EalaY fulaAnK fiY Al$~arafi waAljaladi waAlomanoTiqi","text_ar":"اليَوْمَ عَلَى فُلَانٍ فِى الشَّرَفِ وَالجَلَدِ وَالْمَنْطِقِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one excelled to-day such a one in nobleness and hardiness and speech."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxira","text_ar":"فَخِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxarN","text_ar":"فَخَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He disdained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scorned."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K, TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxarahu Ealayohi","text_ar":"فَخَرَهُ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4."}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","MF","Th","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n33199","headword_ar":"فَخْرٌ","root":"fxr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Glory: excellence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"originally an inf. n.: as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuxorapN","text_ar":"فُخْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohimo","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu la*uw fuxorapK","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَذُو فُخْرَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxorK","text_ar":"فَخْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he possesses glory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellence, above them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or perhaps the meaning of this phrase may be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"verily he has a disposition to boast himself against them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA laka fuxorapu","text_ar":"مَا لَكَ فُخْرَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxoruhu","text_ar":"فَخْرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast not the glory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellence, of this"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Lh, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n33200","headword_ar":"فُخْرٌ","root":"fxr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuxurN","text_ar":"فُخُرٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thickness"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an udder,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with contractedness of the orifices of the teats, and with paucity of milk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}